#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.percentile:106
msgid ""
"Given a vector ``V`` of length ``n``, the q-th percentile of ``V`` is the "
"value ``q/100`` of the way from the minimum to the maximum in a sorted copy "
"of ``V``. The values and distances of the two nearest neighbors as well as "
"the `method` parameter will determine the percentile if the normalized "
"ranking does not match the location of ``q`` exactly. This function is the "
"same as the median if ``q=50``, the same as the minimum if ``q=0`` and the "
"same as the maximum if ``q=100``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.percentile:115
msgid ""
"The optional `method` parameter specifies the method to use when the desired "
"percentile lies between two indexes ``i`` and ``j = i + 1``. In that case, "
"we first determine ``i + g``, a virtual index that lies between ``i`` and "
"``j``, where  ``i`` is the floor and ``g`` is the fractional part of the "
"index. The final result is, then, an interpolation of ``a[i]`` and ``a[j]`` "
"based on ``g``. During the computation of ``g``, ``i`` and ``j`` are "
"modified using correction constants ``alpha`` and ``beta`` whose choices "
"depend on the ``method`` used. Finally, note that since Python uses 0-based "
"indexing, the code subtracts another 1 from the index internally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.percentile:126
msgid ""
"The following formula determines the virtual index ``i + g``, the location "
"of the percentile in the sorted sample:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.percentile:129
msgid ""
"i + g = (q / 100) * ( n - alpha - beta + 1 ) + alpha\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

